##Close-up | the fever clinic under the general attack of "collection" : Late at night, finally quiet

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Liao Yan, a reporter for the paper, in Wuhan

Three layers of surgical gloves, a layer of head cover, a pair of face screen plus protective clothing, from the medical staff access into the isolation channel, before entering the work area.

This series of equipment process, it is difficult to link with the usual "fever clinic" , but the medical staff understand that, in an epidemic, they must do a good secondary protection, to prevent infection.

More than a month on, the city is gripped by a new outbreak of pneumonia, with confirmed cases still rising and no respite in prevention and control.

February 10, Wuhan is the first announcement of the new pneumonia epidemic 42 days, "closed city" on the 19th day. As of 24:00 on the 9th, 1,921 new cases of coronary pneumonia had been reported in Wuhan, bringing the total to 16,902.

Fever clinic is an important checkpoint to judge whether patients with fever are suspected of new pneumonia, and also an important link in epidemic prevention and control.

Since the outbreak, due to the shortage of medical resources, "queuing for three hours" , "see a doctor until midnight" is the patient's impression of the fever clinic in Wuhan Hospital.

Faced with the contradiction between the increasing number of patients and the limited medical resources, the plan given by Wuhan is to construct the Huoshenshan Hospital, the Leishenshan Hospital and the shelter hospital, and to form the triage mechanism for the severe and mild cases.

The tension is easing. With the commissioning of new hospitals and the implementation of various preventive and control measures, the number of fever outpatients in Wuhan Lung Hospital dropped from three to two figures at the same time. The hospital was one of the first three designated hospitals to admit patients with new coronary pneumonia.

Doctors and nurses at the hospital told The Paper www.thepaper.cn  on Feb. 7 that there was a "precipitous" drop in the number of patients attending their fever clinic that day. "instead of seeing 40 patients a morning, I see 40 patients a day, " said one of the doctors.

On the morning of the 10th, Dr. Cheng Zhen, who had just finished the night shift at the fever clinic, said that the patients treated in the two days were similar to those on the 7th. "yesterday, the three of us saw more than 100 patients during the day. Before that, at the peak, the three of US saw more than 300 patients. "

Three days ago, a reporter from the paper visited Wuhan Lung Hospital for ten hours to record the condition of the fever clinic after the patient was triaged. Late that night, here rare "quiet" down.

February 7,3:00 p.m. , Cloudy Day, head-on wind blowing in the face, a little cold.

Before entering the fever clinic, the nurse Song smiled and asked the reporter, "are you afraid? "

"Well, fear of infection. "

"Don't be afraid, you follow me, take precautions, no problem. "

"armed" after Song Xiaoxiao across the room with a bright ultraviolet light into the fever clinic. The corridor behind the door is lined with seats, 16 in all, with room for one more.

In a fever clinic, the sound of footsteps is mixed with the patient's cough and wheezing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A patient in a raincoat

"there are a lot fewer patients today than there were yesterday, " said Song. "probably a lot of patients went to the shelter hospital. ".

Fever symptoms of patients concentrated here, the majority of the elderly. Some patients wear disposable raincoats and surgical masks to get drips on the side of the hallway; others wear goggles.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A woman takes care of her sick mother and sits outside the window after delivering food.

Further into the room, Song Xiaoxiao came to the consultation room, the medical staff's workshop, dispensary in the most inside a small room. The treatment room is the center, and on either side are the observation rooms, which are full of patients, one room with 8 people, the other with 7 people.

Here, health care workers can see through the glass to keep an eye on patients in the room.

"from the clinical diagnosis, the patients in the observation room are basically confirmed patients with new coronary pneumonia. There is a very high risk of cross-infection between the doctors and patients here, " said Dr. Cheng Zhen, who is on duty in the observation room, according to his case of new coronary pneumonia, the main symptom of new coronary pneumonia is fever, from early low fever to persistent high fever, then there will be dyspnea symptoms.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Observation Room of fever clinic

Patients in the observation room, almost everyone standing next to a nearly one-person-high oxygen cylinder, more serious use of the suction machine. Most of them sat on their sickbeds, sometimes lying down, and did not talk. Some patients cry when they see a doctor; others breathe oxygen and are in a daze, their eyes glassy.

A 73-year-old woman lies in the back of the viewing room, her face obscured by an oxygen mask. She hovers over the receiver, hooting as loud as she can.

"She was sent here yesterday by her family, unconscious. The granny tested positive for nucleic acid and was diagnosed, " said Cheng. "there was no way, the bed couldn't be arranged. And the grandmother is in a very serious condition. Even if there were beds, it would be very dangerous to transfer her."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Paramedics are transporting the patient

"nurse, change the needle, " one of the patients in the corridor infusion shouted, the nurse in charge of treatment rushed to the past.

Dispensing, injection and changing the oxygen tank are the nurses'routine work. A nurse pushes a steel oxygen tank, a head above her, toward the patient.

Nurses shuttle back and forth in the corridor, observation room, the treatment room, did not stop to rest. "It was the first day of my support, " said Cao Si, a nurse from the hospital's Tuberculosis Ward 1. "I stood for five or six hours, my back was sore. "

There was a reception room on the east side of the corridor, where two doctors sat, mainly in charge of reviewing the patients'CT reports. There's a long line outside the clinic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The doctor in the admitting room is reviewing the patient's report.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Talking to the nurses at work

There is also a nurse in the reception area who stands at the entrance and is responsible for triage. In addition, she is responsible for opening the door to people who come in from outside.

"It keeps the patients and their families out of the house, " said one nurse, as they slowly worked out how to do so.

More than an hour later, toward evening, patients continued to enter the fever clinic, and to the east of the corridor sat several elderly women, wearing masks, leaning against their seats, infusion, no conversation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To visit the family of the patient's mother

"Look after him for me. He can't hear. You must speak louder. "

Liu Nan, wearing glasses and a hat, told the nurse. Then he handed his father, who was in a wheelchair, to the nurse and walked to the reception room.

The nurse came to lie prone in this old man ear to say loudly: "whine, I want to give you an injection now, the hand does not move. "
The old man's not responding.

The nurse once again loudly said: "Whine, I give you injection, if not comfortable, you tell me Oh. " This time, the old father nodded.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Man Looks after 83-year-old father in observation room

The old man's IV List said age: 83 years old, mainly into a number of immune-enhancing drugs.

The old man put his hands on top of each other. The nurse asked the old man, "are you cold? But you can easily run the needle. " Then the nurse took the old man's hands away, pulled the sleeve to cover the back of his hands as much as possible, and closed the open window beside him.

Not long after, the old man's son rushed back, the nurse explained good drug taking method, he helped the old man into the observation room infusion.

"I'm older, too. I'm 55 years old. My father hasn't been feeling well for a few days, but today he called me to tell me, " Liu said, sighing.

"You have to be careful not to talk to patients, " Liu Nan said repeatedly, as he and his elderly father sat in an observation room with confirmed patients, wearing two layers of surgical masks.

Some of the patients in the observation room sit, some lie down, always with oxygen, the nurses'task is to change the patient, change oxygen.

An elderly man in a purple coat sat in a hallway seat, inhaling oxygen, receiving fluids, a disposable cup beside him, and an unfinished cupcake. Every now and then he would cough and close his eyes again, gasping for breath.

Across from him sat a woman in a disposable yellow raincoat who was also hanging water, pounding her knees with her hands.

"nurse, can I stop? I don't feel well, " she said to the nurse, who looked at her IV list. "You're not done, just wait. "

More than five o'clock in the afternoon, the dinner time arrived, one after another patient's family members came to visit. A middle-aged woman in a simple white cloth protective coat, carrying a insulated lunch box, went straight to the viewing room to see her mother.

"How is your mother doing? "

"not better, but better than staying at home. " The middle-aged Woman's voice looked tired, and before she could ask, she quickly waved her hand away. "No more, no more. "

"She's really struggling, " whispered nurse Zhang Mei, who was outside the observation room. "Her parents have new pneumonia, and her father, who is in his 70s, has been admitted to the hospital, and now she has to run back and forth to take care of her family. "

Through the ward glass, just can see the middle-aged lady standing on the bed, to the mother of the food, the mother will take the food, slowly eat a few mouthfuls. After the mother ate, the middle-aged lady came to the corridor, stood at the window, looking out of the window, a face of melancholy.

At this time, Liu Nan also take care of the old father eating the hospital provided box lunch. Before long, he carried the old father had eaten box rice out, only the rice has been caught in the traces.

Many of the patients treated in hospitals were infected family by family, Zhang Mei said.

At seven o'clock in the evening, the morning nurse can go off duty. Before leaving work, they need to work with the nurses to do a good job of medical supplies, patients, and other handover work. Song and the other nurses were counting the "Kleenex. " "This medicine is very precious, and we count it many times a day, 20 tablets in a small package. " Song said the drug has some inhibitory effect on new coronary pneumonia.

"Xiaoxiao, how many oxygen tanks are there today? " "32. " Song Xiaoxiao and another nurse counted the oxygen tanks at the end of the corridor and found that six bottles were empty.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The oxygen tank at the end of the hall

Around 6:20 p.m. , the fever clinic went quiet. Standing in the treatment room, only to listen to the observation room patients cough, wheezing sound. Out of the exam room, there were only two patients left in the hallway, and he leaned back in his chair to hang water. There's only one doctor left in the intake room.

"yesterday, the hospital was full of patients, there was almost no room in the corridor, many of them were holding transfusion Poles, hanging bags full of transfusion, standing transfusion. " Song Xiaoxiao said that seeing the situation today, for their medical staff, she heaved a sigh of relief at the relative ease of the pressure. Turn around and go back to work.

As night fell, the corridors of the fever clinic became quiet, with only one or two patients receiving fluids. But in the observation room, there were 15 patients lying in bed on oxygen; some with mobile phones with their families are video, there are also patients'families came to accompany, chat.

The grandmother's grandchildren, who were hooked up to the machine, came to care. "Now, the grandmother's oxygen saturation is only 60 percent, and normal people need to reach 95 percent or more, " the doctor said. After hearing what the doctor said, the grandchildren went back to the observation room, to be with my unconscious grandmother.

After 40 minutes, Song Xiaoxiao and colleagues finished the last patient case handover work, ready to leave work. Song Xiaoxiao and Cao Si to the staff channel, work eight hours of her suddenly turned around and said: "off duty, can rest. "

Say, Song Xiaoxiao than a scissors hand.

At 7:00 p.m. , the mid-shift paramedic arrived on time. There are three nurses and one doctor on this shift. They are responsible for all conditions at the fever clinic until 1 am the next day, during which the doctor is on duty until 8 am the next day.

The nurse, Zhang Jie, was dressed a little differently, wearing a disposable blue scrubs over her protective suit, but she walked briskly.

Zhang Jie changed the oxygen, poured hot water, and ran to the clinic's entrance to open the door. "I was on my first night shift today, so I followed the other nurses to see what was going on, " Zhang Jie said, before running out to make a makeshift camp bed for the old man who had been sitting in the hallway getting his purple coat injected.

At night, occasionally a patient or two came over, but after reading the reports, they all went back.

By this time, the corridor was empty before 9 pm.

"The number of patients dropped precipitously today, and it used to be one or two in the morning at night, " said Dr. Chen Nan, who has been on the front lines of the epidemic since the fever clinic opened, february 7th was by far the fewest patients seen.

"The first fever patient I received came from the south China Seafood Market and was over 50 years old, " said Chen. For more than a month, they have encountered many patients with panic and some crying.

At that time, Chen Nan still can"roar"go up two words, wait for a patient to calm down hind, comfort them, continue to see a doctor to them.

When she had just taken a short break, she was informed that a patient in the observation room was about to be transferred to another hospital, and that Zhang Jie was accompanying another nurse to transfer the patient. Zhang Jie wheeled a wheelchair into the viewing room and prepared an oxygen bag.

"Slow down, slow down, " says Zhang Jie, who guides family members to the wheelchair while holding an oxygen bag to keep the oxygen flowing.

Another patient came in half an hour later. He was intubated as soon as he entered the viewing room.

At ten o'clock in the evening, the only sounds heard in the fever clinic were the footsteps of nurses and the coughing and panting of patients. Most of the patients in the viewing room had fallen asleep, but there was an old man in a maroon hat who was still sitting with his oxygen tube in, holding his cell phone and watching TV.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
GRANDPA watching the show on his cell phone after 10:00 at night

Another observation room, Liu Nan's old father is still sitting in the observation room infusion, Liu Nan is lying on the chair outside the corridor to sleep.

The nurses, Zhang Jie and Xie Fang, came to the exam room and for the first time saw them sitting down to rest.

"At work yesterday, our clothes were wet and dry, dry and wet, and we had to go back and forth three times. Today's work is a little bit easier, " Xie Fang said with a smile.

Although they sat in the consulting room, but the hands and busy count "cleats" number, eyes from time to time to look at the situation in the viewing room. "It's all on oxygen now, " she sighed as she looked at the sickly grandmother

Recalling the days of fighting the disease, Zhang Jie said, they often had conflicts and conflicts with patients. "I remember the other day when I was on day shift, one of the patients was so slow because of the injection that he almost hit the head nurse. "

Zhang Jie was so nervous that he didn't want to be shot, but he kept giving the patient the shot.

At 11 p.m. , the lights went out in the viewing room.

Only the grandfather in the Maroon hat still sat, taking out his mobile phone and glancing at it from time to time. "I asked him if he wanted to lie down, and he said it would be more comfortable, " Xie Fang said.

Liu Nan with his old father just left the clinic, ready to go home.

The hours of the night are always very long, with one hour to go until the next day. Xie Fang and Zhang stayed in the exam room, keeping an eye on patients while they sorted out the transition.

"Ding Dong Ding Dong" the bell rang suddenly, Zhang Jie quickly got up to open the door, came in four or five people wearing yellow protective clothing, two of them holding a stretcher.

Across the hall, they headed for the hospital area. A few minutes later, men in Yellow Hazmat suits hurried past, carrying stretchers.

"We just lost a patient in the ICU, " Zhang Jie said.

Suddenly, Zhang Jie and Xie Fang's heart grew heavy.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fever Clinic Hallway at 1:00 a.m

At 1:00 in the morning, out of the fever clinic for more than 10 hours, Wuhan is still so "not noisy" , "not blocked.
The lights are on in the hospital.
